Currently, when a pull request is created with the same source and destination branch of an open pull request the original pull request is overwritten by the latest pull request with the same source and destination branch.

Before the original pull request is overwritten the user who is creating the latest pull request should receive a warning that an existing pull request contains the same source and destination branches.

Example warning 

{noformat}
A similar PR already exists with ID: 123, are you sure you want to overwrite it?
{noformat}

h3. Issue Summary

When trying to migrate Bitbucket issues to a free Jira Cloud instance the following error occurs:
{noformat}
Error Messages: [You can't update role actors for this project as it's on the Jira Software Free plan.]{noformat}
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a repository under a workspace you are an admin in Bitbucket;
 # Sign up for a free Jira Cloud instance;
 # Integrate Bitbucket to your Jira Cloud instance;
 # Create an issue on your repository;
 # Navigating to *Repository settings* > *Issues* > *Import & export*, click on *Start migration*;
 # Select your Jira site;
 # Type in the name of the project and click *Migrate issues*.

h3. Expected Results

Issue migration to a free Jira cloud instance should complete with success.
h3. Actual Results

Migration is finished with errors:

The below exception is thrown in the log file:
{noformat}
Error Messages: [You can't update role actors for this project as it's on the Jira Software Free plan.]
{noformat}
h3. Workaround

It is possible to migrate the issues if you temporarily upgrade your Jira instance to a standard/premium plan. On your Jira site:
 # Click on the *Cog icon* > *Billing* > *Manage subscriptions*;
 # Click *{color:#0747a6}Change{color}*, right next to your plan tier;
 # Select *Standard* or *Premium* plan;
 # Proceed to import the Bitbucket issues to Jira;
 # After the migration is done, roll your plan back to free subscription;
